# paint.type AI Manifest (Level 1)

This is the AI manifest for the `src/` directory (Level 1) of paint.type.

## Purpose

This manifest describes the purpose and structure of the `src/` directory.

## Authority Split

- **Central protocol authority:** `standards/` repository
- **Local integration authority (this directory):** src/ specific configurations

## Subdirectories\n\n| Directory | Layer | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `bridges/` | 2 | |\n| `contracts/` | 2 | |\n| `host_core/` | 2 | |\n| `host/` | 2 | |\n| `core/` | 2 | |\n| `ui/` | 2 | |\n| `errors/` | 2 | |\n| `paint_core/` | 2 | |\n| `aspects/` | 2 | |\n| `interface/` | 2 | |\n| `definitions/` | 2 | |\n\n## Invariants

1. All A2ML state files must live in `.machine_readable/` ONLY, never in the repo root.
2. Each directory at layer 1 must have its own `0.1-AI-MANIFEST.a2ml`.
3. Each directory must have a `README.adoc` describing purpose, contents, and function.
4. SPDX license identifiers must be consistent across all files (AGPL-3.0-or-later).

## Startup Checklist for Agents

1. Read this file (`0.1-AI-MANIFEST.a2ml`).
2. Read `README.adoc` for directory overview.
3. For subdirectories, navigate to their respective manifest files.
4. Never edit `.machine_readable/` files directly.
